   <mods:abstract>John Jay's letter to him of the 31st March has given him much pain. Gives
            an account of various transactions up to this time and explains his actions on them.
            Infers from John Jay's letter that his uncle believes he has improperly detained money
            he ought to have paid. Whether this opinion be correct or incorrect, he ought not to
            continue as John Jay's agent. Encloses an account drawn up between them which includes
            Peter's bonds to Augustus Jay, which he now considers discharged.</mods:abstract>
